  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering involves several key components:\n\n1. International Regulations\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- UN Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Framework\n\n2. Key Legislative Acts\n- Bank Secrecy Act\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- USA PATRIOT Act\n- Money Laundering Control Act\n\n3. Compliance Requirements\n- Customer due diligence\n- Suspicious activity reporting\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) procedures\n\n4. Criminal Penalties\n- Significant financial fines\n- Potential imprisonment\n- Asset seizure\n- Criminal prosecution\n\n5. Regulatory Bodies\n- Financial Crimes Enforcement Network (FinCEN)\n- Securities and Exchange Commission\n- Federal law enforcement agencies\n\n6. Prevention Mechanisms\n- Enhanced screening processes\n- Risk-based approaches\n- International information sharing\n- Ongoing transaction tracking\n\n7. Jurisdictional Variations\n- Different countries have unique AML regulations\n- Cross-border enforcement challenges\n- Varying legal standards and penalties\n\nThe framework aims to detect, prevent, and prosecute financial crimes.",
